definitions.definition: A hollow muscular organ of the neck of mammals situated just below where the tract of the pharynx splits into the trachea and the oesophagus . It is involved in breath control and protection of the trachea, and, as it houses the vocal cords , sound production .

main_definition: ( anatomy , zootomy ) A hollow muscular organ of the neck of mammals situated just below where the tract of the pharynx splits into the trachea and the oesophagus . It is involved in breath control and protection of the trachea, and, as it houses the vocal cords , sound production .
